  <sharedRules>
    <rule name="Terror" id="6ab6-05fc-f3ac-7fe3" hidden="false">
      <alias>Terror X</alias>
      <description>Weapons with Terror X cause enemy units hit by them to have to roll terror tests, after attacking, if any models in the target unit were killed by a attack, that unit must roll 2d5 against the value, adding or subtracting a bonus depending on the type of unit hit. See Faction Rule: Terror for more detail</description>
      <comment>Weapon Keyword</comment>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Self Repairing" id="e1eb-2603-e99e-b97c" hidden="false">
      <description>If a model has this ability, then at the end of that units turn, roll a d10 for each missing wound for each roll of 10+, that wound is recovered.


For units with downed models with multiple wounds, sum the entirety of the downed models wounds.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Terror" id="7679-8baf-220a-5196" hidden="true">
      <comment>Army rule With lore</comment>
      <description>*Few mortal men have fought the Untended, those who have are shocked, left in states of panic and delirium from horrors wrought from a past better left forgotten.*

Some weapons and abilities will have a “Terror X+” keyword, after attacking with these weapons, if any models in the target unit were killed by the attack, that unit must roll 2d10 against X+ adding or subtracting values based on that units type on the [Terror Modifier Table]

If a unit fails its Terror Test, then that unit is now terrified until the end of the round, and several modifiers now apply.

The unit must reroll charge rolls and take the lower result.
The unit must fall back if possible
at the end of the round, for each missing model in that unit, roll a d10, on a 1, another model is removed from play.</description>
      <modifiers>
        <modifier type="set" value="false" field="hidden">
          <conditions>
            <condition type="atLeast" value="1" field="selections" scope="force" childId="8b56-1ed1-7f7d-2738" shared="true" includeChildSelections="true"/>
          </conditions>
        </modifier>
      </modifiers>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Terror" id="a555-8a51-062c-b31d" hidden="false">
      <comment>Army rule Without lore</comment>
      <description>Some weapons and abilities will have a “Terror X+” keyword, after attacking with these weapons, if any models in the target unit were killed by the attack, that unit must roll 2d10 against X+ adding or subtracting values based on that units type on the [Terror Modifier Table]


If a unit fails its Terror Test, then that unit is now terrified until the end of the round, and several modifiers now apply.


The unit must reroll charge rolls and take the lower result.
The unit must fall back if possible
at the end of the round, for each missing model in that unit, roll a d10, on a 1, another model is removed from play.</description>
      <modifiers>
        <modifier type="set" value="true" field="hidden">
          <conditions>
            <condition type="atLeast" value="1" field="selections" scope="force" childId="8b56-1ed1-7f7d-2738" shared="true" includeChildSelections="true"/>
          </conditions>
        </modifier>
      </modifiers>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Faction Rule: Self Repairing" id="9790-3a48-3321-98f6" hidden="true">
      <comment>With lore</comment>
      <description>“… There are rumors on board, spread by drunken sailors no doubt, of metal monsters that can rise from the dead, but how can a machine repair itself? I have ordered the crew to stop spreading such lies, and personally I do not believe a word of it.” - Cptn. Clancy, Last recorded log of the UHS Pillbug, recovered from fleet wreckage


Some of the untended threat repair themselves by unknown and cryptic means. 


If a model has this ability, then at the end of the turn, roll a d10 for each missing wound for each roll of 10+, that wound is recovered.


For units with downed models with multiple wounds, sum the entirety of the downed models wounds.</description>
      <modifiers>
        <modifier type="set" value="false" field="hidden">
          <conditions>
            <condition type="atLeast" value="1" field="selections" scope="force" childId="8b56-1ed1-7f7d-2738" shared="true" includeChildSelections="true"/>
          </conditions>
        </modifier>
      </modifiers>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Faction Rule: Self Repairing" id="8f7a-d3d6-3c11-b2fa" hidden="false">
      <comment>Without lore</comment>
      <description>Some of the untended threat repair themselves by unknown and cryptic means. 


If a model has this ability, then at the end of the turn, roll a d10 for each missing Health Point for each roll of 10+, that Health Point is recovered.

if a model did not revive at the end of a turn, it is permenantly removed from play and cannot be revived later

For units with downed models with multiple Health Point, sum the entirety of the downed models wounds.</description>
      <modifiers>
        <modifier type="set" value="true" field="hidden">
          <conditions>
            <condition type="atLeast" value="1" field="selections" scope="force" childId="8b56-1ed1-7f7d-2738" shared="true" includeChildSelections="true"/>
          </conditions>
        </modifier>
      </modifiers>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Reclamation" id="ef05-88aa-f4a8-bb01" hidden="false">
      <description>When a model uses a weapon with this keyword, if any attack from that weapon destroyes a enemy model, the attacking model may roll 1d10, on a 6+ it may regain 1 wound</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Intra-Exile" id="c544-a92b-4bb4-71da" hidden="false">
      <description>When firing a weapon with this special rule, a hit roll of 10 bypasses saves, a wound roll of 10 instantly kills the model that is being targeted by this weapon. Against vehicles, a penetrating roll of 10 always causes a penetrating hit, regardless of the targets armor value.</description>
    </rule>
  </sharedRules>
